{
  "stem": "19895.3",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And surviving in the ghetto itself was something of a miracle, because no food, very-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] reduced sanitation and so on.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Vaguely, just a foggy memory of always trying to give hope, my father was always giving hope.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so was my mother, that it will be over.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It will be over.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "We-- we never lost hope.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But we knew that the-- that the rules and-- and incidents and the circumstances were tightening, tightening.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then we pretty much were aware that something else happened in the country, the Jews must have been taken away, because we couldn't have any contact with family.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And then we heard the news that deportations started.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the city of Budapest and the Budapest Jewish Council had serious negotiations with governments, and-- and all kind of negotiation, some of it which involved property and money, which I found later on how-- how it went, later on meaning after World War II was over.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I was also working as a 16-year-old little boy, before they took me away, in the Budapest Jewish Councils they needed a messenger service.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And a couple of young boys like myself, maybe two dozen or so, were given different armband, which was a blue armband written on it that the Budapest Jewish Council.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And that gave us also a certificate, which was countersigned by the police department that we could move around in the city more freely.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And one of these encounters, it is tragicomical.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "I was one day at the Jewish Council.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And-- we were given bicycles that we were traveling with to locations in the city.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And I had to deliver a key in an envelope with a letter accompanying it.",
      "word_count": 15
    }
  ],
